# Integrate AI Hedge Fund into TradingView UI

Integrate the AI Hedge Fund (multi-agent LLM stock analysis system) as a new "Hedge Fund" tab within the existing TradingView UI desktop application. The hedge fund agents will use data already available in the app (yfinance prices, Screener fundamentals) instead of the external `financial-datasets-api`.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **LLM Provider Configuration**: The hedge fund agents require an LLM API key (e.g., OpenAI, Groq, Ollama). We need to decide how API keys are managed:
> - **Option A**: Read from `.env` file in the project root (simplest, current approach in ai-hedge-fund)
> - **Option B**: Add a settings panel in the UI where users can input/save API keys
> - **Recommendation**: Start with Option A (`.env` file), add UI settings later if needed.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Indian vs US Stock Tickers**: The AI hedge fund was designed for US stocks (AAPL, MSFT, etc.) while your TradingView UI is for NSE/Indian stocks (RELIANCE, TCS, etc.). The agents use `financial-datasets-api` data models (SEC filings, US-style financial metrics). When we replace the data layer:
> - **Price data**: Works fine — yfinance supports `.NS` tickers
> - **Financial metrics**: We'll map Screener.in data fields to the `FinancialMetrics` model the agents expect
> - **Line items** (detailed financials like capex, depreciation, etc.): We'll extract from Screener's P&L/balance sheet/cash flow tables
> - **Insider trades & company news**: These came from the US-focused API. We can replace with your existing announcement/news data, or skip these agents initially
> - **Market cap**: Available from Screener summary data

> [!WARNING]
> **Data Coverage Gap**: Some agents (e.g., Warren Buffett, Sentiment) rely heavily on data types that may not map perfectly from Screener.in (e.g., `insider_trades`, `company_facts`). These agents will either produce partial analysis or gracefully skip missing data sections. Do you want me to:
> - **A)** Include ALL agents and gracefully handle missing data (some may produce incomplete analysis)
> - **B)** Only include agents that work well with available data (Technical, Fundamentals, Valuation, Growth, News Sentiment via announcements)
> - **Recommendation**: Option A — include all agents, gracefully handle missing data

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **Ollama Support**: Do you want to support local LLMs via Ollama, or only cloud API providers (OpenAI, Groq, etc.)?
> 2. **Default Analysts**: Should the hedge fund tab default to a subset of analysts (e.g., Rakesh Jhunjhunwala, Technical, Fundamentals) or all 18?
> 3. **Backtesting**: The original app has backtesting capability. Should we include it in this integration or skip it for now?

