### Component 1: Data Bridge Layer

The critical integration piece — replaces `ai-hedge-fund/src/tools/api.py` with a new module that fetches data from yfinance and DuckDB/Screener instead of `financial-datasets-api`.

#### [NEW] [data_bridge.py](file:///D:/projects/stock_data_pipelines/ai-hedge-fund/src/tools/data_bridge.py)

A drop-in replacement for `api.py` functions, backed by local data sources:

| Original Function | New Data Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `get_prices()` | yfinance via existing `YFinanceSourceAdapter` | Convert yfinance OHLCV to `Price` model |
| `get_financial_metrics()` | Screener DuckDB (`screener_financials.duckdb`) | Map Screener summary/ratios → `FinancialMetrics` |
| `search_line_items()` | Screener DuckDB (P&L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow tables) | Map table rows → `LineItem` model |
| `get_insider_trades()` | Return empty list (data not available for NSE) | Agents gracefully handle empty data |
| `get_company_news()` | Announcements DuckDB (`announcements.duckdb`) | Map announcements → `CompanyNews` model |
| `get_market_cap()` | Screener summary "Market Cap" field | Parse Indian number format |
| `prices_to_df()` | Same logic, unchanged | |
| `get_price_data()` | Same logic, unchanged | |

