### Component 2: Backend API Routes

Add hedge fund API endpoints to the existing `server.py`.

#### [MODIFY] [server.py](file:///D:/projects/stock_data_pipelines/tradingview_ui/server.py)

Add these new API routes:

| Route | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/hedge-fund/agents` | GET | List available analyst agents |
| `/api/hedge-fund/models` | GET | List available LLM models |
| `/api/hedge-fund/run` | POST | Run analysis (SSE streaming response) |
| `/api/hedge-fund/status` | GET | Get current analysis progress |

The `/run` endpoint will:
1. Accept JSON body: `{ tickers, selected_analysts, model_name, model_provider, start_date, end_date, initial_cash }`
2. Run the LangGraph workflow in a background thread
3. Stream SSE progress events back to the frontend
4. Return final decisions and analyst signals on completion

Key design decisions:
- Use Python's `ThreadingHTTPServer` pattern (already used by server.py) — run the graph in a background thread, poll progress
- Reuse the existing `AgentProgress` handler system from `src/utils/progress.py`
- Set environment variables to force `data_bridge` mode before importing hedge fund modules

